## 5. Testing Frequency and Triggers

### 5.1 Scheduled Testing

| AI System Category | Testing Frequency |
|-------------------|-------------------|
| High-risk (automated decisions on eligibility, employment, credit) | Quarterly |
| Medium-risk (recommendations, personalisation, scoring) | Every 6 months |
| Low-risk (content generation, summarisation, internal tools) | Annually |

### 5.2 Event-Triggered Testing

An unscheduled bias audit must be conducted when:

- A new AI model version is deployed or fine-tuned
- Training data is updated or expanded significantly
- A complaint or report of discriminatory outcomes is received
- The AI system is applied to a new use case or population
- Regulatory guidance changes (e.g., OAIC or AHRC guidance on AI fairness)
{% if tranche2_aware %}- POLA Act Tranche 2 introduces mandatory bias testing requirements{% endif %}

