## 6. Bias Metrics

{{ business_name }} will measure and report on the following fairness metrics:

| Metric | Definition | Use Case |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| **Demographic parity** | Equal positive outcome rates across all groups | General fairness screening |
| **Equal opportunity** | Equal true positive rates across groups (given actual positives) | Employment and eligibility decisions |
| **Equalised odds** | Equal true positive and false positive rates across groups | High-risk automated decisions |
| **Calibration** | Predicted probabilities match actual outcomes across groups | Scoring and risk assessment systems |
| **Predictive parity** | Equal positive predictive values across groups | Screening and triage systems |
| **Individual fairness** | Similar individuals receive similar outcomes | Case-by-case assessment systems |

