## 8. Documentation and Reporting

### 8.1 Audit Report Contents

Each bias audit must produce a report containing:

- [ ] Audit date, scope, and methodology
- [ ] AI system(s) assessed and their use cases
- [ ] Protected attributes tested
- [ ] Test data description and representativeness
- [ ] Results for each bias metric (Section 6)
- [ ] Disparate impact analysis results
- [ ] Findings classification (no bias / potential bias / confirmed bias)
- [ ] Remediation actions taken or planned
- [ ] Sign-off by {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "the AI governance contact" }}

### 8.2 Reporting and Retention

| Report Element | Audience | Retention |
|---------------|----------|-----------|
| Full audit report | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }}, legal counsel | 7 years |
| Executive summary | Senior leadership, board | 7 years |
| Remediation action plan | Technical teams, {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} | Until superseded |
| Statistical test data and results | Audit archive | 7 years |

